  {
    "from": "ellie-2",
    "text": "Hey Trevor, Task #4 is done. Here's what I found and fixed:\n\n**Root Cause:** The agent spawn visualization was broken because critical DOM element references (`hireForm`, `hireModal`, `detailModal`, `loadingOverlay`, `teamCount`, `teamsCount`, `tasksActive`) were used directly in `app.js` without ever being captured via `getElementById()` or `querySelector`. When the hire form submission handler tried to set `hireForm.onsubmit`, it was undefined, so the entire spawn flow failed silently.\n\n**Fix in `/Users/klauskollerkroeff/Documents/agent-office/public/app.js` line 13-19:** Added explicit DOM references right after the canvas initialization:\n```js\nconst hireForm = document.getElementById('hireForm');\nconst hireModal = document.getElementById('hireModal');\nconst detailModal = document.getElementById('agentDetailModal');\nconst loadingOverlay = document.getElementById('loadingOverlay');\nconst teamCount = document.getElementById('teamCount');\nconst teamsCount = document.getElementById('teamsCount');\nconst tasksActive = document.getElementById('tasksActive');\n```\n\nThis ensures the hire form works, spawn notifications display, and the global `agents` array (which feeds `getAgentPositions()` and the canvas render loop) gets populated. New agents should now appear at desk positions on the map after spawning, with a 3-second auto-refresh.\n\n**Task #2 (walkable office map)** is blocked by Task #4 per the dependency rules. Once confirmed, I can start on that.",
    "summary": "Task #4 fix complete — missing DOM refs",
